This study investigates whether an additional remote follow-up of patients with implantable cardioverter-defibrillators (ICDs) has beneficial effects on Quality of life (QoL), levels of anxiety and depression and device acceptance.

 Patients are randomized to either conventional in-office FU only or additional remote surveillance, follow-up duration is 12 months.

